race.comment: SETHEUS (4) is an honest type who took while to get on the board but scored a determined win last time. Looks well placed here and can make it back-to-back wins now. PRESERVATOR (6) ran an improved race third-up and fitter again looks ready to show best. Will be winding up late. DIVINE TURF (8) is going better than last couple suggest. Aided by the claim and can feature on best figures. ZIGGI ROCKS (3) returns from a spell. Placed in a recent Ballarat Synthetic jump-out. Opened last campaign with a ninth at Avoca over 1200m. In the mix. PATSY'S STAR (1) was unwanted in the market when resuming last start at this track over 1454m and finished seventh. Fitter and can contest for a place.
